cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the evaluation of computational language models in predicting human judgments of sentence acceptability. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of neural models and word embeddings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the use of n-gram statistics and simple language features to capture acceptability variance. Finally, it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it evaluates the performance of predictive neural models.
